label Day3_Redemption:
    scene bg street1 day with longblink
    "It's going to be okay."
    play music Bright_Opening
    "Sure, things got fucked up, but I think anyone could see I'm not a bad guy."
    "I just let things get to my head and I made some mistakes. I accept that."
    scene bg ext school day with blink
    "But I can explain myself. At least Nozomi will hear me out."
    "So I'll apologize to both of them. I guess make some kind of peace offering. Even Hiroko won't say no to that."
    "Yeah. It's gonna be okay."
    stop music fadeout 5.0
    # "He's rationalized his behaviour. He's not the bad guy and he just had some terrible lapses of judgement."
    # "All he's got to do is smooth things over. Repeat how sorry he is, maybe make a peace offering?"
    scene bg classroom day with longblink
    "... Where are they?"
    play music Eons
    "First period's started and neither of them have showed up?"
    "Did they seriously both skip out of class to avoid me?"
    "What other reason could it be that they're both missing today?"
    # "... But as he gets to school he soon realizes that neither Nozomi nor Hiroko are coming to class today."
    # "Feeling deflated, Kyou pretty much tunes out the morning lessons..."
    with blink
    "It takes me out of the morning lessons. I can't focus at all."
    play sound schoolbell
    "And the bell sounding for lunch takes forever."
    "What do I even do with myself for the rest of the day?"
    show Sayori neutral at center
    "Maybe... yeah, her." with dissolve
    "Sayori normally goes up to the roof with Nozomi and Hiroko, but without them she seems to be staying to lunch at her desk."
    "I wouldn't normally speak to her. Or, anyone I guess. Unless I had to."
    show Sayori annoyed_right
    "But if anyone knows about Nozomi and Hiroko it'll be her." with dissolve
    s "What?"
    "Her response to seeing me gets my back up. Just gotta power through it..."
    ks neutral "Hey. I just wanted to know if you heard from Nozomi?"
    ks "Or Hiroko. I guess."
    s uniform_folded "You guess. Do you guess that you may in some manner be responsible for their absence?" with dissolve
    s annoyed "I cannot imagine you would feel concern for Hiroko were it not for a guilty conscience..." with dissolve
    "Oh, man. What did they tell her? Does she know what happened yesterday?"
    stop music fadeout 5.0
    ks sigh "Look, I just wanted to know if they said anything, that's all."
    s irritated "They said many things. We are friends, which I understand is something of a foreign word to you." with dissolve
    ks "Come on, don't be like that."
    s uniform angry_right "{cps=20}I will most certainly \"be like that\" when the person I am speaking to is such irredeemable {nw}{/cps}" with dissolve
    extend "FILTH!" with vpunch
    play music Rain
    "I can feel the eyes of everyone in the room on me as Sayori raises her voice, cutting through the background din of the classroom to get everyone's attention."
    "It stuns me for a moment. I don't think Sayori has ever shouted at anyone before."
    "But I can't just leave it at that. I'm not talking to her without a good reason."
    ks "J-just... tell them I said sorry, okay? I want to set things right."
    "Sayori glares at me a moment longer before opening her mouth again."
    s uniform_handup irritated "Unbelievable. But I will tell you this: If you are truly remorseful then you should be thinking less about yourself and more about those you have hurt." with dissolve
    ks surprised "What?"
    "Did I just hear that right?"
    ks frown "Sayori, I told you I want to apologize. Maybe give them something, I don't know, I just... I just want them to come back."
    s annoyed_right "And what do you suppose THEY want? Have you considered that?" with dissolve
    ks "What..."
    show Sayori irritated
    "Sayori then waves her hand dismissively as she turns away from me." with dissolve
    s "You waste my time. Leave."
    scene bg corridor day with blink
    "Fucking..."
    "With everyone's attention on us, I couldn't bear staying in that room a moment longer."
    "But what the fuck, Sayori?"
    scene bg rooftop with blink
    "So I guess I'm lunching on the roof today."
    "I'll sit where Nozomi usually sits. She's not going to be using it today, after all."
    "But what am I supposed to do if I can't even apologize? Is Nozomi going to be as stubborn as Sayori just now?"
    "Hell, they can't avoid me forever."
    "Still... I mean, it hasn't even been a day. They'll calm down tomorrow. Or the day after, or next week."
    "When things aren't so raw, I'll get my chance."
    "I just need to be patient..."
    stop music fadeout 5.0
    scene bg classroom day with blink
    "The afternoon classes feel tense."
    play music Audience
    "I can feel people's cold gaze upon me as the hours pass. From people who normally wouldn't notice me at all."
    "It's like the atmosphere that I left at lunch never dissipated one bit when I came back in."
    "Does EVERYONE fucking hate me around here?"
    play sound schoolbell
    scene bg classroom eve
    show Sayori neutral at right
    with blink
    s "Stand."
    s sleeptalk "... Bow." with dissolve
    hide Sayori
    "The final bell can't come soon enough." with dissolve
    t "Mr. Koyama? A moment of your time, please."
    ks surprised "H-huh?!"
    "The hell? My homeroom teacher never talks to me."
    "I'd better see what he wants..."
    ks confused "Sir?"
    stop music fadeout 10.0
    "He politely ignores me while he watches the other students file out of the room."
    "... So it's THAT kind of talk?"
    play sound doorclose
    "I watch with him as the last of the stragglers closes the door behind them, and only then does Mr. Kobayashi begin speaking."
    t "So... this afternoon I was called to an emergency meeting with our principal."
    t "He informed me that he had received two strongly-worded complaints from the parents of two of your current classmates."
    "And at the mention of that, I can feel the ground sink underneath me."
    play music Sorrow
    t "Now I want to assure you, Kyou, that you are not in any trouble. There is no talk of suspending you, and we have no evidence that you have done anything untoward."
    "... What?"
    t "However, the parents of these students have made it very clear that they no longer feel safe in this classroom."
    "... WHAT?"
    t "So although the school board has no intention of issuing any mark upon your record, Mr. Koyama, they have proposed a compromise."
    "\"No intention of issuing a mark upon my record\". So he means to tell me I'm not being punished..."
    t "We thought it would be in everyone's best interests if you were to be moved to one of the other third year classrooms."
    "But I AM being punished!"
    t "We feel all three of you will be able to continue your studies for the upcoming entrance exams with minimal disruption."
    "Minimal disruption... Yeah, like, who cares if I'm in this class or that one? It's all the same to a friendless loser like me, huh, Kobayashi."
    t "But I want to be clear once again: You are not in trouble. This is still your choice, and we'll need your full written consent to facilitate this action."
    "This is fucking BULLSHIT! A couple girls get a little scared and that's all it takes to get me out?"
    t "So, you've been patient listening to all this, and I know it's a lot to take in. But I'd like to know your thoughts."
    "Everyone's lost their goddamned minds!"
    t "... Kyou?"
    ks frown "U-uh, right. Well..."
    "What the fuck am I supposed to do? Fight it?"
    ks sigh "I don't know what to say, Sir."
    "I could tell dad about it. Raise some hell and get the school to back down."
    t "Take a little time, but I'm afraid I'm going to need an answer by the end of the week."
    "But what's the fucking point? Dad's too tired and useless to really have my back anyway."
    "And if I don't agree to this now I'll be keeping those two away from school for longer. That's only going to make things worse for myself."
    ks sigh "Nah, it's fine. I'll sign."
    "I'll sign the fucking document. Why delay the inevitable?"
    play sound papers
    "And as I pen my name, my now former homeroom teacher smiles faintly at me."
    t "Thank you for understanding, Koyama. And try not to let it get you down."
    t "Anyway, please report to class 3-C starting tomorrow. Everything else will be taken care of..."
    scene bg street1 eve with blink
    "And with that, I bowed to him and got myself out of there as fast as I politely could."
    "Like, what else is there to say?"
    scene bg k bedroom eve with blink
    "Crashing to my bed, I feel a numbness all over my body."
    "A deep pain in my gut that might never leave me."
    "It's all so fucking unfair!"
    stop music fadeout 5.0
    scene bg blackscreen with longdissolve
    pause 2.0
    jump Day4_Redemption

label name_alter:   #Allows the player to submit their own name for Sayori's alter and checks it against a few common sense criteria for validity
    $alt_name_valid = False
    while alt_name_valid == False:
        menu:
            "Aiko":
                $alt_name = "Aiko"
            "Megumi":
                $alt_name = "Megumi"
            "Yuri":
                $alt_name = "Yuri"
            "Invent your own":
                $alt_name = renpy.input(_("Type the name you want (12 characters or fewer):"), length=12)
                $alt_name = alt_name.strip()
                $alt_name = alt_name.capitalize()
        # The following checks the string presented for names that Kyou would consider inappropriate for use
        if alt_name == "Sayori" or alt_name == "Sayo" or alt_name == "Watanabe": #"Sayo" is never used as a nickname for Sayori, but is included anyway
            "... Not her name. A DIFFERENT name."
        elif alt_name == "Hiroko" or alt_name == "Hiro" or alt_name == "Homura" or alt_name == "Nozomi" or alt_name == "Nozo" or alt_name == "Akemi":
            "Naming her after one of her friends would be just too weird. And confusing."
        elif alt_name == "Kobayashi": # How about naming her after the homeroom teacher? :D
            "What, my homeroom teacher? Pass."
        elif alt_name == "Kyou" or alt_name == "Koyama": # Err....
            "... Wait, no, that's MY name!"
        elif alt_name == "Penlight" or alt_name == "Fembot" or alt_name == "Gynoid" or alt_name == "Ginoide" or alt_name == "Robot" or alt_name == "Linterna": #Uhh...
            "I don't think naming her after a thing would go down very well."
        elif len(alt_name) < 2: #Put some effort into it, geez
            "That's not a name..."
        else:
            $alt_name_valid = True
        if alt_name_valid == True:
            $alt_name = alt_name.lower() # Here's a rudimentary attempt to stop the player from calling Sayori really rude names >:(
            if (alt_name.count("bitch") > 0 or alt_name.count("fuck") > 0 or alt_name.count("cunt") > 0 or alt_name.count("slut") > 0 or alt_name.count("retard") > 0
            #Really not going to be an exhaustive list, but can't hurt to call out a few slurs someone might mindlessly try entering. The anti-asian ones in particular
            or alt_name.count("tranny") > 0 or alt_name.count("faggot") > 0 or alt_name.count("nigger") > 0 or alt_name.count("chink") > 0 or alt_name.count("jap") > 0
            or alt_name.count("cum") > 0 or alt_name.count("whore") > 0 or alt_name.count("slave") > 0 or alt_name.count("thrall") > 0 or alt_name.count("servant") > 0
            or alt_name.count("assistant") > 0 or alt_name.count("sirviente") > 0 or alt_name.count("asistente") > 0 # Also a few less rude but still pretty inappropriate things fall into this category
            or alt_name.count("esclav") > 0 or alt_name.count("perra") > 0 or alt_name.count("zorra") > 0 or alt_name.count("puta") > 0
            or alt_name.count("mierda") > 0 or alt_name.count("gilipollas") > 0 or alt_name.count("pendej") > 0 #Including some derogatory Spanish words too
            or alt_name.count("coño") > 0 or alt_name.count("culer") > 0 or alt_name.count("puñetas") > 0 or alt_name.count("pelotud") > 0
            or alt_name.count("bolud") > 0 or alt_name.count("conche") > 0):
                "Uh... what? Why would I give her a name like that?"
                $alt_name_valid = False
            elif alt_name.count("sayori") > 0 or alt_name.count("watanabe") > 0: #Checks to see if Sayori's names are included anywhere in the string submitted
                "Eh, I'd better not mention her name at all, really."
                $alt_name_valid = False
            elif (alt_name.count("a") == 0 and alt_name.count("e") == 0 and alt_name.count("i") == 0 and alt_name.count("o") == 0 and alt_name.count("u") == 0
                and alt_name.count("y") == 0 and alt_name.count("á") == 0 and alt_name.count("é") == 0 #If there's none of these characters in the name, it's probably nonsense.
                and alt_name.count("í") == 0 and alt_name.count("ó") == 0 and alt_name.count("ü") == 0 and alt_name.count("ú") == 0):
                "That doesn't make any sense."
                $alt_name_valid = False
            else:
                $alt_name = alt_name.title()
            if alt_name.isalpha() == False: # No numbers or other weird characters. Only letters and spaces
                $namecheck = alt_name
                $namecheck = namecheck.replace(" ", "")
                if namecheck.isalpha() == False:
                    "That sounds more like the kind of name you'd give to a robot or something."
                    $alt_name_valid = False
            if alt_name == "Iroyas": #Sayori spelled backwards? Sure, why not...
                "What? That's... oh, I see what's going on. Alright, then."
        if alt_name_valid == False:
            "Gotta think of something else..."
        # Yes, the script doesn't check for the name "Akiko" or "Risa". Kyou doesn't know either of them well enough to think it weird if he calls her that
        # Ditto for any other named extras in the script.
        # Still though, possible easter eggs abound if Kyou names her after anyone known to the other girls...
    return
